### [Leviticus Chapter 15](../../../bib/kjv/lev015.htm#001.md)

[Leviticus 15:1](../../../bib/kjv/lev015.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">lev 15:1</span></span>

This chapter would seem to take its place more naturally before [Lev
12:1-8](../../../bib/kjv/lev012.htm#001.md), with the subject of which it
is inmediately connected. Compare especially [Lev
12:2](../../../bib/kjv/lev012.htm#002.md) with [Lev
15:19](../../../bib/kjv/lev015.htm#019.md). It stands here between two
chapters, with neither of which has it any close connection.

[Leviticus 15:13](../../../bib/kjv/lev015.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">lev 15:13</span></span>

The mere cessation of the issue does not make him clean: he must wait
seven days, etc., preparatory to his offering sacrifice.

[Leviticus 15:16](../../../bib/kjv/lev015.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">lev 15:16</span></span>

Most of the ancient religions made a similar recognition of impurity and
of the need of purfication.

[Lev 15:17](../../../bib/kjv/lev015.htm#017.md)

Every garment - Compare [Jde 1:23](../../../bib/kjv/jde001.htm#023.md).

[Leviticus 15:24](../../../bib/kjv/lev015.htm#024.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_024">lev 15:24</span></span>

This must refer to an unexpected occurrence. Intercourse during the
acknowledged period was a heavy crime, and was to be punished by
"cutting off" [Lev 18:19](../../../bib/kjv/lev018.htm#019.md); [Lev
20:18](../../../bib/kjv/lev020.htm#018.md); [Eze
18:6](../../../bib/kjv/eze018.htm#006.md).

[Leviticus 15:31](../../../bib/kjv/lev015.htm#031.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_031">lev 15:31</span></span>

This solemn admonition is addressed to Moses and Aaron, see [Lev
15:1](../../../bib/kjv/lev015.htm#001.md).

[Lev 15:31](../../../bib/kjv/lev015.htm#031.md)

My tabernacle - Strictly, "my dwelling-place" משׁכן mı̂shkān, as in [Lev
8:10](../../../bib/kjv/lev008.htm#010.md); [Lev
17:4](../../../bib/kjv/lev017.htm#004.md); [Lev
26:11](../../../bib/kjv/lev026.htm#011.md). The word rendered "tabernacle"
elsewhere in Leviticus is properly "tent." See the [Exo
26:1](../../../bib/kjv/exo026.htm#001.md) note.

